Greeceâ€™s  Energy Ministry  will name
next week a company, or possibly two, chosen to conduct seismic
surveys for oil and natural gas in the Ionian Sea and south of
Crete,  Imerisia  reported, without citing anyone.  The company or companies will be chosen from four of the
original eight that submitted applications to conduct the
surveys, the newspaper said. The four are:  TGS-Nopec Geophysical
Co. ASA (TGS) ,  Petroleum Geo-Services ASA (PGS) , Spectrum Geo Ltd. and  ION
Geophysical Corp. (IO) , Imerisia said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
